Key Match Events: Brandon Glover bowled a slower legcutter to dismiss Rilee Rossouw in the tenth over.
Glover dismissed David Miller and Wayne Parnell in the 16th over, with van der Merwe completing a sensational catch to dismiss Miller.
Stephan Myburgh scored 34 runs in the powerplay.
Colin Ackermann scored an unbeaten 41 off 26 balls, with 21 runs coming in the last two overs.
Roelof van der Merwe took a dramatic catch to dismiss David Miller.
Post-Match Reflections: Brandon Glover expressed happiness with the team's performance and noted the strong South African influence in the Netherlands squad.
Glover reflected on his journey and the hard work that led to his success in the tournament.
Glover mentioned that the match might have been Stephan Myburgh's last for the team.
Glover emphasized the team's belief in competing with top international teams.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Adelaide pitch was two-paced and offered some grip, which Glover utilized effectively.
This T20 World Cup marks the end of Ryan Campbell's stint as the head coach of Netherlands.
